# Chat

`TxChatList` renders a transcript from `ChatMessageModel[]`. It delegates each row to `TxChatMessage`, supports Markdown content, lazy image thumbnails, optional staggered entry animation, and emits a normalized `imageClick` payload when an attachment thumbnail is clicked.

Reviewed against `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/chat/src/types.ts`, `TxChatList.vue`, `TxChatMessage.vue`, `TxChatComposer.vue`, `TxTypingIndicator.vue`, and the chat component tests.

## Basic Usage

### ChatList
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="ChatChatListDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import type { ChatMessageModel } from '@talex-touch/tuffex/chat'
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const messages = ref<ChatMessageModel[]>([
    { id: 'system-1', role: 'system', content: 'Markdown is enabled.', createdAt: 1_705_000_000_000 },
    {
      id: 'user-1',
      role: 'user',
      content: 'Review this release cover.',
      attachments: [{ type: 'image', url: '/cover.svg', name: 'cover.svg' }],
    },
    { id: 'assistant-1', role: 'assistant', content: 'Looks ready.\n\n```ts\nconst status = "ready"\n```' },
  ])
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxChatList :messages="messages" :markdown="true" @image-click="console.log" />
  </template>
---
:::

## Interaction Contract

- `TxChatList` preserves the order of `messages` and renders each message by its stable `id`.
- `markdown` defaults to `true`; message bodies are passed to `TxMarkdownView`. Set `markdown=false` to render plain text.
- `stagger` defaults to `true`; the list wraps rows in `TxStagger`. Disable it for virtualized or frequently re-sorted transcripts.
- `createdAt` is formatted only after mount, avoiding SSR/client time mismatch.
- Image attachments render as native `button type="button"` thumbnails with lazy-loaded images.
- `imageClick` always includes `{ url, name, messageId }`, so the host can open a preview, download, or audit the source message.

## API

### Data Models

#### ChatMessageModel

| Field | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `id` | `string` | required | Stable message key used by `TxChatList`. |
| `role` | `'user' \| 'assistant' \| 'system'` | required | Message role and row alignment. |
| `content` | `string` | required | Markdown or plain text body. |
| `createdAt` | `number` | - | Epoch timestamp rendered as `HH:mm` after mount. |
| `avatarUrl` | `string` | - | Optional avatar image for the row. |
| `attachments` | `ChatMessageAttachment[]` | - | Image attachments rendered as thumbnails. |

#### ChatMessageAttachment

| Field | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `type` | `'image'` | required | Current attachment kind. |
| `url` | `string` | required | Image URL used by the thumbnail and click payload. |
| `name` | `string` | - | Accessible image alt text and click payload label. |

### Props

#### TxChatList

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `messages` | `ChatMessageModel[]` | required | Transcript messages, rendered in array order. |
| `markdown` | `boolean` | `true` | Render message content through `TxMarkdownView`. |
| `stagger` | `boolean` | `true` | Animate rows through `TxStagger`. |

#### TxChatMessage

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `message` | `ChatMessageModel` | required | Single message row. |
| `markdown` | `boolean` | `true` | Render content as Markdown or plain text. |

### Events

#### TxChatList

| Event | Params | Description |
|------|--------|-------------|
| `imageClick` | `{ url: string, name?: string, messageId: string }` | Re-emitted from `TxChatMessage` when an image attachment thumbnail is clicked. |

#### TxChatMessage

| Event | Params | Description |
|------|--------|-------------|
| `imageClick` | `{ url: string, name?: string, messageId: string }` | Emitted when an image attachment thumbnail is clicked. |

### Slots

#### TxChatList

No public slots are exposed; customize individual rows through `TxChatMessage` when you need alternate rendering.

#### TxChatMessage

| Slot | Props | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `avatar` | `{ message: ChatMessageModel }` | Replaces the avatar image/fallback. |
| `header` | `{ message: ChatMessageModel }` | Replaces the timestamp header. |
| `content` | `{ message: ChatMessageModel }` | Replaces Markdown/plain body rendering. |

### Exposed Methods

No public instance methods are exposed.

